<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>PANEL DISCUSSION FROM SOCIALISM 2007</b></font><br>
<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="5"><b>Confronting empire</b></font><p>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">June 22, 2007 | Pages 8 to 12</font><p>

<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b><a href="636_08_Mejia.shtml">PREVIOUS SPEAKER</a> | <a href="636_08_Will.shtml">NEXT SPEAKER</a></b><br>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><a href="636_08_Pilger.shtml">John Pilger</a> | <a href="636_08_Sanchez.shtml">Mart&iacute;n Sanchez</a> | <a href="636_08_Wasfi.shtml">Dahlia Wasfi</a> | <a href="636_08_Mejia.shtml">Camilo Mej&iacute;a</a> | <a href="636_08_Scahill.shtml">Jeremy Scahill</a> | <a href="636_08_Will.shtml">Rob Will</a> | <a href="636_08_Geier.shtml">Joel Geier</a><p>
<p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1">- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -</font></p>

<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="5"><b>Jeremy Scahill</b></font><p>

<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="2"><i>Independent journalist who reported from Iraq before the invasion, and author of the best-selling book </i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&amp;location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBlackwater-Rise-Worlds-Powerful-Mercenary%2Fdp%2F1560259795%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Dbooks%26qid%3D1182362998%26sr%3D1-1&amp;tag=socialistwork-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325" target="_blank">Blackwater: The Rise of the World's Most Powerful Mercenary Army</a>.</font><p>

<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="3">I THINK we have a real crisis in this country that seldom gets recognized. We have allowed the powerful, the rich, the Democratic and Republican Cheech-and-Chong machine--I stole that from Immortal Technique--to define the political context through which we view the world.<p>
We need to remove 9/11 from our memories for a moment, and look at a perfect trajectory of mass slaughter in Iraq that extends back many decades, and extends to both the Democratic and Republican regimes that have ruled this country.<p>

<table width="270" align="right"><tr><td>
<table width="258" cellpadding="12" cellspacing="0" align="right" border="2" hspace="8" bordercolor="006699" bgcolor="#FFCC66"><tr><td>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4" color="#990000"><b>What else to read</b></font><p>
